<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,535,776]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,644,669]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the original description the 
<typeStatus box="[803,890,645,669]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">syntype</typeStatus>
series included male(s) too, therefore it can be stated with certainty that a part of the specimens (
<typeStatus box="[708,873,679,704]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
) remains undiscovered. 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1239,680,704]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Aethalotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horni">
<emphasis box="[1147,1239,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">A. horni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species distributed in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[425,482,716,741]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">India</collectingCountry>
and in 
<collectingCountry box="[581,700,716,741]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. Its diagnostic characters were discussed and illustrated and a detailed description was presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Scudder" box="[578,755,751,776]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" refString="Scudder, G. G. E. (1963) A revision of the genus Astacops sensu lat. (Hemiptera: Lygaeidae). Pacific Insects, 5 (2), 315 - 415." type="journal article" year="1963">
Scudder (
<number box="[685,746,751,776]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
